<div class="container mt-3 text-center">
  <h1 class="display-4 font-weight-bold ">WELCOME TO THE NEST</h1><br>


  <div class="row justify-content-center">
    <div class="col-md-6 mx-5 my-3">
      <h6 class="font-weight-bold"> It's 5:30am on a snowy morning. This is the year you get in shape, and so far you've been good about sticking to your new exercise routine...<br></h6>
      <p>But this morning your motivation is waning. You didn't get a great night's sleep, and your bed is so warm. You can skip just one day without it being a big deal, right?<br><br> Those bargains are familiar to many fitness aspirants, as is the low-level shame that accompanies skipping a workout and breaking a promise you have made to yourself. But the difficult task of starting and maintaining a fitness regimen could be made easier by not going it alone.<br><br>The accountability and motivation of a group exercise dynamic may be just what you need to keep moving toward your fitness goals. </p>
    </div>  
  </div>

  <h3 class="perm text-muted mb-3">Where do you want to go?</h3>

  <div class="row justify-content-center pb-3 mt-2">
    <div class="card mx-4" style="width: 10rem;">
      <%= image_tag "group_ph.jpg", class: "landing" %>
      <div class="card-body">
      <%= link_to "Groups", groups_path, class: "btn btn-lg btn-warning" %>
     </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mx-4" style="width: 10rem;">
      <%= image_tag "user_ph.jpg", class: "landing" %>
      <div class="card-body">
      <%= link_to "Users", users_path, class: "btn btn-lg btn-warning" %>
     </div>
    </div>
  </div>  
  
</div>